  "instructions": [
    "Mix sesame seeds, flaxseeds, yeast, water, olive oil, and salt in a large bowl. Knead until dough forms.",
    "Let the dough ferment for at least 8 hours or up to overnight.",
    "Divide the dough into small balls. Roll them out flat using rice flour or bread flour as needed.",
    "Preheat oil in a pan over medium heat. Cook the sesame seed buns on both sides until golden brown, about 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Serve warm with your favorite vegan dips and dressings."
